That looks good.

42
00:03:06,052 --> 00:03:07,921
How is it? Do you like it?

43
00:03:07,987 --> 00:03:08,955
Tamagoyaki.

44
00:03:09,022 --> 00:03:11,057
Yay! Cool...

45
00:03:11,124 --> 00:03:14,027
You look cool, awesome.

46
00:03:14,093 --> 00:03:15,061
One, two...

47
00:03:15,128 --> 00:03:20,667
<i>The wooden table in the commercial
was also built by the group.</i>

48
00:03:21,734 --> 00:03:22,902
So, how is it?

49
00:03:24,437 --> 00:03:26,272
<i>One week earlier.</i>

50
00:03:26,339 --> 00:03:28,508
Good morning. Nice to meet you.

51
00:03:28,575 --> 00:03:29,475
KAWASAKI

52
00:03:29,542 --> 00:03:31,778
Good morning. I look forward to today.

53
00:03:31,844 --> 00:03:33,780
Good morning. Let's do some work today.

54
00:03:34,547 --> 00:03:37,183
Was building this table
your idea, Mr. Kokubun?

55
00:03:37,250 --> 00:03:38,751
Yes, it was.

56
00:03:38,818 --> 00:03:42,288
For some reason, I just said...

57
00:03:43,489 --> 00:03:46,359
"Let's try building a table."

58
00:03:47,393 --> 00:03:49,395
When I said that,

59
00:03:51,164 --> 00:03:53,366
the others were like,
"That's a good idea!"

60
00:03:54,367 --> 00:03:59,872
After all, our company motto is
"Sweat, work, and experience."

61
00:04:00,406 --> 00:04:02,642
That's why I decided to sweat and work.

62
00:04:04,644 --> 00:04:07,714
<i>Kokubun will build the tabletop.</i>

63
00:04:13,953 --> 00:04:15,888
It feels like I'm actually working.

64
00:04:16,389 --> 00:04:17,724
I'm actually working.

65
00:04:22,328 --> 00:04:24,831
The tree has curves here too.

66
00:04:29,235 --> 00:04:35,642
Have there ever been any entertainers
that have built their own sets?

67
00:04:35,708 --> 00:04:38,678
I feel a sense of attachment to it though.

68
00:04:39,379 --> 00:04:42,715
