<i>Joshima works on the legs of the table.</i>

75
00:05:11,511 --> 00:05:13,313
I just want to clean it up.

76
00:05:13,379 --> 00:05:15,448
This really shows your personality.

77
00:05:16,282 --> 00:05:18,651
This is something you do quietly

78
00:05:18,718 --> 00:05:21,688
but since we're on TV,
I have to say something.

79
00:05:22,689 --> 00:05:24,324
That looks good. Thank you.

80
00:05:24,390 --> 00:05:26,392
How about this part...

81
00:05:26,459 --> 00:05:27,293
Very meticulous.

82
00:05:31,064 --> 00:05:34,534
<i>Matsuoka works on putting it together.</i>

83
00:05:36,703 --> 00:05:38,137
-All right.
-Okay.

84
00:05:39,605 --> 00:05:42,475
I'm the one
that shouldn't be able to do this.

85
00:05:43,176 --> 00:05:44,143
Yeah.

86
00:05:44,210 --> 00:05:47,980
When it was the five of us,
I was the worst at this.

87
00:05:48,047 --> 00:05:50,516
Now that there's only three of us,
so I have no choice.

88
00:05:51,084 --> 00:05:52,218
Okay.

89
00:05:57,190 --> 00:05:58,191
Okay. All right.

90
00:05:59,192 --> 00:06:00,293
Okay.

91
00:06:05,098 --> 00:06:07,300
This is cute.

92
00:06:07,367 --> 00:06:09,068
Wow. If you had more time...

93
00:06:09,135 --> 00:06:11,537
It looks handmade. It looks good.

94
00:06:12,472 --> 00:06:14,307
Yeah, this is cute.

95
00:06:15,875 --> 00:06:19,879
<i>Matsuoka sands the table,
so the children won't hurt themselves.</i>

96
00:06:22,348 --> 00:06:23,716
This is nice.

97
00:06:23,783 --> 00:06:26,252
It's nice and round.

98
00:06:28,020 --> 00:06:29,722
Where should we stamp the table?

99
00:06:30,656 --> 00:06:32,759
<i>The members
put their finishing touches on it.</i>

100
00:06:32,825 --> 00:06:33,893
Oh I see.

101
00:06:35,695 --> 00:06:37,497
-Here I go.
-Right in the middle?

102
00:06:37,563 --> 00:06:38,531
Good.

103
00:06:38,598 --> 00:06:39,832
It's a bit diagonal.

104
00:06:41,033 --> 00:06:42,268
That could look good.

105
00:06:46,372 --> 00:06:48,174
I want to take a picture.

106
00:06:48,841 --> 00:06:50,510
-Done.
-It worked!

107
00:06:50,576 --> 00:06:52,278
-Cool.
-I did it. It worked.

108
00:06:52,812 --> 00:06:56,716
<i>This is a new TOKIO Inc. logo
they designed.</i>

109
00:06:57,683 --> 00:07:00,520
Please be ready to clap for me.

110
00:07:01,854 --> 00:07:03,222
{\an8}Here we go.

111
00:07:03,289 --> 00:07:04,123
{\an8}Congratulations.

112
00:07:09,529 --> 00:07:10,563
Take a picture of me.

113
00:07:13,232 --> 00:07:14,867
What are you taking pictures of?

114
00:07:14,934 --> 00:07:16,669
You should be taking pictures of me.

115
00:07:18,337 --> 00:07:19,405
I think it's ready.

116
00:07:19,472 --> 00:07:20,306
Really?

117
00:07:21,174 --> 00:07:22,008
Here!

118
00:07:23,476 --> 00:07:25,445
It's barely on there!

119
00:07:27,680 --> 00:07:28,781
Hey!

120
00:07:29,348 --> 00:07:31,184
This is really bad.

121
00:07:31,884 --> 00:07:34,921
Everything was going well
until now. Sorry.

122
00:07:35,488 --> 00:07:38,424
Well, it actually has
its own flavor, so it's okay.

123
00:07:38,491 --> 00:07:39,859
You can try another spot.

124
00:07:39,926 --> 00:07:41,093
Yeah, I'll do it again.

125
00:07:41,160 --> 00:07:44,330
I have no problem showing my mistakes.

126
00:07:44,397 --> 00:07:45,832
This is a mistake.

127
00:07:46,966 --> 00:07:50,236
This one has a lot more smoke coming out.

128
00:07:51,471 --> 00:07:53,706
-I think it's ready.
-No, no, no...

129
00:07:54,574 --> 00:07:55,608
Here!

130
00:07:55,675 --> 00:07:57,076
See? It's perfect.

131
00:07:57,143 --> 00:08:00,012
There it is!

132
00:08:00,780 --> 00:08:02,181
I'm relieved.

133
00:08:02,248 --> 00:08:04,016
This looks very cool.

134
00:08:05,651 --> 00:08:06,953
Good.

135
00:08:07,019 --> 00:08:09,455
A table of success born from a mistake.

136
00:08:13,159 --> 00:08:14,794
<i>During this time,</i>

137
00:08:14,861 --> 00:08:20,199
<i>Kokubun was working at TOKIO Inc.,
while writing new songs.</i>

138
00:08:31,410 --> 00:08:33,613
<i>In charge of his own group,</i>

139
00:08:33,679 --> 00:08:36,849
<i>he works on a big
music TV program's opening theme song.</i>

140
00:08:50,730 --> 00:08:55,034
When I feel the creative juices flowing,
I'll bring a MIDI keyboard with me.

141
00:08:55,868 --> 00:08:58,938
I'll do this when I have some time.

142
00:09:01,374 --> 00:09:03,543
I do like to create things.

143
00:09:03,609 --> 00:09:06,012
No matter how I look at it.

144
00:09:06,078 --> 00:09:08,648
No matter how I look at it,
I love creating things.

145
00:09:09,649 --> 00:09:11,350
It just pops in my mind.

146
00:09:11,417 --> 00:09:14,654
Those sorts of ideas
that make things interesting.

147
00:09:16,722 --> 00:09:21,193
That's why I do things
I'm not even asked to do.

148
00:09:21,694 --> 00:09:22,895
It's like...

149
00:09:24,063 --> 00:09:26,933
I'm showing proof
I'm participating in something.

150
00:09:26,999 --> 00:09:27,934
Yeah.

151
00:09:30,670 --> 00:09:33,673
I guess I feel strongly about that.

152
00:09:37,843 --> 00:09:39,145
<i>Rehearsal Day.</i>

153
00:09:39,211 --> 00:09:41,180
JUNE
TOKYO, TENNOZU

154
00:09:41,247 --> 00:09:44,450
Good morning. I look forward to today.

155
00:09:44,517 --> 00:09:45,418
Good morning.

156
00:09:45,484 --> 00:09:46,586
Thanks for coming.

157
00:09:46,652 --> 00:09:49,055
Thank you.

158
00:09:49,121 --> 00:09:51,591
Thank you.

159
00:09:51,657 --> 00:09:54,760
It's been a long time
since I've done something like this.

160
00:09:55,528 --> 00:09:57,997
<i>Due to COVID-19,</i>

161
00:09:58,064 --> 00:10:01,400
<i>Kokubun hasn't been able to meet
his band members until today.</i>

162
00:10:09,075 --> 00:10:11,544
It's been a while. Thank you for coming.

163
00:10:11,611 --> 00:10:12,578
Have you been busy?

164
00:10:12,645 --> 00:10:14,280
No, I'm completely free.

165
00:10:14,347 --> 00:10:15,414
-Really?
-Yeah, it's really bad.

166
00:10:15,481 --> 00:10:16,782
It can't be that bad...

167
00:10:16,849 --> 00:10:17,950
What about concert tours?

168
00:10:18,017 --> 00:10:20,453
-Those dried up.
-Really? That's too bad.

169
00:10:20,519 --> 00:10:24,190
That's why I focus on
composing music right now.

170
00:10:24,256 --> 00:10:26,559
I compose just a few songs as a hobby.

171
00:10:26,626 --> 00:10:29,495
Sometimes I'm able to complete them.

172
00:10:29,562 --> 00:10:31,364
Then that's a good thing.

173
00:10:31,430 --> 00:10:32,531
I teach music too.

174
00:10:32,598 --> 00:10:33,733
I see.

175
00:10:33,799 --> 00:10:35,768
I never thought it'd turn out like this.

176
00:10:35,835 --> 00:10:37,770
-I know what you mean.
-Yeah.

177
00:10:37,837 --> 00:10:42,108
<i>Kokubun understands the lives of
his band members as if they were family.</i>

178
00:10:42,174 --> 00:10:43,876
I was so happy too.

179
00:10:45,177 --> 00:10:47,480
Excuse me.
I look forward to working with you.

180
00:10:47,546 --> 00:10:50,716
Hello, may I introduce myself?

181
00:10:50,783 --> 00:10:55,354
I'm Taichi Kokubun. We established
TOKIO Inc. in April of this year.

182
00:10:55,421 --> 00:10:56,288
Nice to meet you.

183
00:11:00,292 --> 00:11:05,097
I've been thinking about the band name.

184
00:11:10,002 --> 00:11:11,771
It's a bit long,

185
00:11:11,837 --> 00:11:14,907
but it means
"make use of an opportunity immediately."

186
00:11:14,974 --> 00:11:17,009
That's what it means if you rephrase it.

187
00:11:17,076 --> 00:11:18,878
My interpretation of it is

188
00:11:18,944 --> 00:11:22,815
"create something out of your passions."

189
00:11:22,882 --> 00:11:25,351
And that's why I created this band.

190
00:11:25,418 --> 00:11:26,352
Thank you.

191
00:11:29,255 --> 00:11:30,256
That's nice.

192
00:12:04,190 --> 00:12:06,158
So cool.

193
00:12:06,859 --> 00:12:07,693
Awesome.

194
00:12:09,295 --> 00:12:12,698
Could the people in the brass section...

195
00:12:13,532 --> 00:12:15,334
dance or anything like that?

196
00:12:18,237 --> 00:12:19,972
Can the guitars do like...

197
00:12:20,039 --> 00:12:25,678
"I thought the guitars would be rock-like,
but it unexpectedly sounds like..."

198
00:12:25,745 --> 00:12:28,748
That's the way I'd like it to be.

199
00:12:28,814 --> 00:12:30,549
Just really that kind of mood.

200
00:12:31,751 --> 00:12:33,219
That looks cool.

201
00:12:34,453 --> 00:12:35,988
It's really cool.

202
00:12:37,289 --> 00:12:39,458
<i>He also designed the logo for the band.</i>

203
00:12:40,760 --> 00:12:42,828
I won't fit a medium...

204
00:12:49,068 --> 00:12:50,302
That looks good on you.

205
00:12:50,369 --> 00:12:52,004
Thank you.

206
00:12:53,839 --> 00:12:56,108
That looks cool. You look like a DJ.

207
00:12:56,175 --> 00:12:57,009
Totally a DJ.

208
00:13:01,647 --> 00:13:03,415
{\an8}Six minutes left!

209
00:13:03,482 --> 00:13:06,886
{\an8}Are there any staff members
without anything to do?

210
00:13:07,386 --> 00:13:08,721
Please raise the roof.

211
00:13:08,788 --> 00:13:10,222
Yay!

212
00:13:10,289 --> 00:13:12,725
If you do, it'll energize the people here.

213
00:13:12,792 --> 00:13:14,193
Okay!

214
00:13:14,260 --> 00:13:15,795
Thank you.

215
00:13:25,538 --> 00:13:29,775
{\an8}<i>TOKIO was formed back in 1990.</i>

216
00:13:30,409 --> 00:13:36,549
{\an8}<i>At the time, the group consisted of
Kokubun, Joshima and Matsuoka only.</i>

217
00:13:36,615 --> 00:13:39,084
{\an8}<i>Strangely enough,
the exact same members now.</i>

218
00:13:40,119 --> 00:13:41,086
{\an8}HELLO, THIS IS TOKIO!

219
00:13:41,153 --> 00:13:45,958
{\an8}<i>Living together at a boardinghouse,
they focused on their CD debut.</i>

220
00:13:49,028 --> 00:13:52,531
<i>Their dream came true four years later.</i>

221
00:13:53,365 --> 00:13:57,937
<i>But it wasn't smooth sailing
from the beginning.</i>

222
00:13:59,972 --> 00:14:05,611
We wanted to get first place
right after we debuted.

223
00:14:06,111 --> 00:14:11,083
When you debut in Johnny's,
you usually get first place.

224
00:14:11,150 --> 00:14:13,485
Most artists will usually get first place.

225
00:14:14,053 --> 00:14:16,121
That's how I thought it would be for us.

226
00:14:16,188 --> 00:14:20,926
There were younger artists that
debuted after us, like Kinki Kids and V6.

227
00:14:20,993 --> 00:14:23,295
And they all got first place
like it was nothing.

228
00:14:24,530 --> 00:14:28,934
<i>The group decided to stick to
their own way of doing things.</i>

229
00:14:29,902 --> 00:14:32,771
<i>They didn't wear
colorful clothing meant for pop idols,</i>

230
00:14:32,838 --> 00:14:35,541
<i>but wore T-shirts
or nothing at all at times.</i>

231
00:14:36,642 --> 00:14:40,946
<i>They've always shown
their true selves this whole time.</i>

232
00:14:45,150 --> 00:14:46,619
We were almost naked.

233
00:14:46,685 --> 00:14:49,955
I always thought
we should cover up a little more.

234
00:14:50,022 --> 00:14:53,993
When we were younger...

235
00:14:54,627 --> 00:14:57,730
We wore the colorful clothing
young idols wear now.

236
00:14:57,796 --> 00:15:01,467
But along the way,
we stopped wearing that kind of clothing.

237
00:15:02,468 --> 00:15:04,370
{\an8}The opening starts
with something like this...

238
00:15:04,436 --> 00:15:06,171
{\an8}<i>LEVECHI NA HITO, MITSUKETA</i> FILMING

239
00:15:07,239 --> 00:15:10,910
{\an8}<i>After his idol days,
he worked as a presenter on TV.</i>

240
00:15:10,976 --> 00:15:14,446
{\an8}<i>No matter what genre.
He carved out his own career path.</i>

241
00:15:14,513 --> 00:15:16,181
{\an8}<i>DANSHI GOHAN</i> FILMING

242
00:15:16,248 --> 00:15:17,549
{\an8}That's good.

243
00:15:18,150 --> 00:15:20,819
{\an8}<i>KOKUBUN TAICHI NO OKIRAKU SANPO
~HAPPY GO LUCK~</i> FILMING

244
00:15:21,587 --> 00:15:24,757
{\an8}<i>Kokubun has a record
number of TV appearances,</i>

245
00:15:24,823 --> 00:15:27,693
{\an8}<i>topping first place six years in a row.</i>

246
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:30,229
{\an8}<i>TOKIO TERRACE</i> FILMING

247
00:15:30,296 --> 00:15:32,564
{\an8}Nothing comes to mind using this.

248
00:15:33,866 --> 00:15:37,336
I can't imagine coming up
with ideas while using this.

