<i>August.</i>

250
00:15:43,542 --> 00:15:44,643
Can I get in the car?

251
00:15:44,710 --> 00:15:45,844
Yes, please.

252
00:15:46,745 --> 00:15:48,247
Am I riding in this one?

253
00:15:48,314 --> 00:15:49,682
Excuse me.

254
00:15:53,352 --> 00:15:57,189
<i>Kokubun was put in charge of
a cheerleading team for the Tokyo Olympics</i>

255
00:15:57,256 --> 00:15:59,692
<i>by a certain television station.</i>

256
00:16:07,633 --> 00:16:10,469
{\an8}<i>While gathering information
on the athletes,</i>

257
00:16:10,536 --> 00:16:13,872
{\an8}<i>he also learned a few things
he could apply to his own work.</i>

258
00:16:20,779 --> 00:16:25,584
The beauty of sports
isn't just about the medals.

259
00:16:25,651 --> 00:16:27,987
It's the process.

260
00:16:28,053 --> 00:16:30,589
The beauty of the process
of getting to this point.

261
00:16:30,656 --> 00:16:33,225
That's what moves me.

262
00:16:34,026 --> 00:16:36,528
I believe the process
is extremely important.

263
00:16:36,595 --> 00:16:41,734
That's what makes it easy for me
to give it my best at whatever I do.

264
00:16:43,802 --> 00:16:47,306
I believe it's important
to be inspired by other people.

265
00:16:48,173 --> 00:16:49,274
Good work.

266
00:16:49,341 --> 00:16:50,409
I look forward to it.

267
00:16:50,476 --> 00:16:51,910
Yes, thank you.

268
00:16:57,649 --> 00:16:58,884
JUNE WANGAN STUDIO

269
00:16:58,951 --> 00:16:59,885
<i>On this day,</i>

270
00:16:59,952 --> 00:17:04,256
<i>a meeting that would predict
the future of TOKIO Inc. took place.</i>

271
00:17:05,958 --> 00:17:07,493
We'll do everything here.

272
00:17:07,559 --> 00:17:08,627
Here?

273
00:17:08,694 --> 00:17:10,295
Yes. We'll take it here first.

274
00:17:10,362 --> 00:17:11,196
Thank you.

275
00:17:12,364 --> 00:17:16,602
<i>TOKIO Inc. is starting a project to create
things by partnering with organizations.</i>

276
00:17:16,668 --> 00:17:18,804
<i>There were many applications.</i>

277
00:17:22,274 --> 00:17:25,010
Wow. Look at all these applications.

278
00:17:25,077 --> 00:17:28,247
There's so many of them, I'm so grateful.

279
00:17:29,314 --> 00:17:31,784
<i>They had more applications
than anticipated.</i>

280
00:17:31,850 --> 00:17:33,752
Start with number one.

281
00:17:33,819 --> 00:17:34,720
Oh, from the bottom.

282
00:17:34,787 --> 00:17:37,623
We'd like you to narrow it down
to 10 to 15 companies.

283
00:17:37,689 --> 00:17:40,459
Please start choosing ones
that interest you.

284
00:17:40,526 --> 00:17:42,261
I'll take a close look on my own.

285
00:17:42,327 --> 00:17:43,462
Yeah, I agree.

286
00:17:43,529 --> 00:17:45,531
I'd like to take my time to look at these.

287
00:17:45,597 --> 00:17:47,900
If you see something...

288
00:17:47,966 --> 00:17:48,934
Something we like...

289
00:17:49,001 --> 00:17:50,803
And you need more information,

290
00:17:50,869 --> 00:17:54,873
please tell me what number
and I'll send you their information.

291
00:17:54,940 --> 00:17:56,508
So please let me know.

292
00:17:58,210 --> 00:18:00,245
<i>Even while working on other projects,</i>

293
00:18:00,312 --> 00:18:03,048
<i>they take their time
looking at each proposal.</i>

294
00:18:09,588 --> 00:18:12,458
With all these people joining us

295
00:18:12,524 --> 00:18:16,295
and working together to create something...

296
00:18:17,796 --> 00:18:20,232
I feel like there's a vision.

297
00:18:20,799 --> 00:18:22,801
I feel closer to them.

298
00:18:22,868 --> 00:18:27,306
It's the idea of pursuing one thing

299
00:18:27,372 --> 00:18:30,342
and creating something from scratch.

300
00:18:30,409 --> 00:18:33,212
It feels like
there's a deep meaning to it all.

301
00:18:34,146 --> 00:18:38,217
<i>There's a memory
that Joshima will never forget.</i>

302
00:18:40,619 --> 00:18:44,156
<i>It happened 29 years ago.</i>

303
00:18:44,223 --> 00:18:48,160
<i>It was before TOKIO debuted
with their first CD.</i>

304
00:18:48,227 --> 00:18:51,029
AUGUST 28
HARAJUKU

305
00:18:51,096 --> 00:18:55,834
When was the last time
I walked down this road?

306
00:18:55,901 --> 00:18:57,636
It's the same.

307
00:18:58,170 --> 00:19:00,539
<i>It was their first handshake event</i>

308
00:19:00,606 --> 00:19:02,941
<i>which took place in this
Johnny's Shop in Harajuku.</i>

309
00:19:03,008 --> 00:19:04,910
It's exactly the same as before.

310
00:19:05,744 --> 00:19:07,112
Wow.

311
00:19:07,679 --> 00:19:13,385
Before we debuted as TOKIO,
we had a handshaking event here.

312
00:19:13,452 --> 00:19:17,990
We wanted to raise our recognition
and see if there were any fans.

313
00:19:18,056 --> 00:19:22,361
"How many people could we attract?"
All of us were so excited.

314
00:19:22,427 --> 00:19:25,864
Our boardinghouse wasn't too far
from here.

315
00:19:26,598 --> 00:19:27,566
We were curious.

316
00:19:27,633 --> 00:19:29,768
"It would be amazing
if there was a line here."

317
00:19:29,835 --> 00:19:35,807
We peeked outside the window
and saw there was a little bit of a line.

318
00:19:35,874 --> 00:19:38,043
"What is that?"

319
00:19:38,110 --> 00:19:41,813
"What do we do if it's for us?"

320
00:19:41,880 --> 00:19:44,683
When we came, it was for us.

321
00:19:44,750 --> 00:19:48,387
The fans were lining up.

322
00:19:48,453 --> 00:19:51,690
They saw us and were like, "Wow!"

323
00:19:52,491 --> 00:19:56,261
It's one memory I have
seeing them through the window.

324
00:19:56,828 --> 00:19:59,031
It was very touching.

325
00:19:59,865 --> 00:20:01,567
That brings back memories.

326
00:20:02,134 --> 00:20:03,769
Wow...

327
00:20:05,304 --> 00:20:06,805
In that way...

328
00:20:07,673 --> 00:20:09,508
They're emotions I can't let go of

329
00:20:10,375 --> 00:20:13,779
in the history of TOKIO...

330
00:20:13,845 --> 00:20:16,381
This place is a holy ground for us.

331
00:20:17,182 --> 00:20:18,417
Yeah.

332
00:20:18,483 --> 00:20:21,053
I'm so grateful to all the fans.

333
00:20:22,287 --> 00:20:23,255
Yeah.

334
00:20:24,656 --> 00:20:27,159
That made me really happy.

335
00:20:30,262 --> 00:20:36,702
<i>The joy of creating something
with someone left a mark in his heart.</i>

336
00:20:43,141 --> 00:20:47,746
<i>They're now working on a photoshoot
to promote the udon chain restaurant.</i>

337
00:20:49,915 --> 00:20:51,683
Don't pan the camera.

338
00:20:53,452 --> 00:20:55,420
Yes, thank you.

339
00:20:55,487 --> 00:20:56,855
I don't...

340
00:20:57,756 --> 00:20:59,391
I don't usually get embarassed.

341
00:20:59,458 --> 00:21:01,093
But these make me so embarassed.

342
00:21:01,159 --> 00:21:03,295
-Sorry.
-Seriously...

343
00:21:03,362 --> 00:21:05,464
Yeah, that looks good.

344
00:21:08,667 --> 00:21:09,901
<i>During this photoshoot,</i>

345
00:21:09,968 --> 00:21:13,505
<i>there was one member
who did exactly what the cameraman said.</i>

346
00:21:13,572 --> 00:21:15,240
<i>It was Matsuoka.</i>

347
00:21:17,109 --> 00:21:18,577
After that...

348
00:21:19,411 --> 00:21:21,313
Okay, I got it.

349
00:21:22,347 --> 00:21:25,550
Smile like you're sending
a message to the children.

350
00:21:25,617 --> 00:21:27,886
That's great. Perfect.

351
00:21:28,453 --> 00:21:31,490
"Let's do our best!" "Be healthy!"

352
00:21:31,990 --> 00:21:33,859
That's wonderful.

353
00:21:34,660 --> 00:21:37,829
<i>What memories
have left an impression on Matsuoka?</i>

354
00:21:37,896 --> 00:21:38,830
Nice.

355
00:21:41,800 --> 00:21:43,869
{\an8}-It's okay, you can sit there.
-Thank you.

356
00:21:43,935 --> 00:21:47,306
{\an8}<i>Next time, the one side of Matsuoka
that we don't know.</i>

357
00:21:48,073 --> 00:21:52,577
{\an8}"If I can hold my breath
until I get out of this tunnel,

358
00:21:52,644 --> 00:21:55,213
{\an8}I'll make it into Johnny's."
I did that a lot.

359
00:21:55,280 --> 00:21:57,983
{\an8}Of course. Very much a coward.
I'm like a Pomeranian.

360
00:21:58,050 --> 00:22:00,085
{\an8}Well... If left alone, I would die.

361
00:22:01,286 --> 00:22:04,289
{\an8}<i>He's strict yet nice.</i>

362
00:22:05,891 --> 00:22:09,428
{\an8}If I brought your family here,
your dad points would go up.

363
00:22:10,128 --> 00:22:12,864
{\an8}What am I saying on this program?

